<subSubSection id="FDAA651F061A2E57FF48FF8EFC8F25B3" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="350" pageId="48" pageNumber="349" type="description">
<paragraph id="B50F3694061A2E56FF48FF8EFCA3263A" blockId="48.[151,1437,601,880]" pageId="48" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061A2E56FF48FF8EFEB327F1" bold="true" box="[199,345,673,699]" pageId="48" pageNumber="349">Description.</emphasis>
Carapace wider than long, convex, smooth, regions not defined, covered by short dense tomentum. Rostrum tridentate lateral teeth broadly triangular, rounded, median tooth shorter, sharper, at lower level, slightly deflexed; supraorbital margin continues interrupted by weak supraorbital tooth and similar postorbital tooth, suborbital tooth more prominent. Anterolateral margin armed with 2 similar blunt teeth and strong subhepatic tooth visible dorsally between postorbital corner and first anterolateral tooth; margin between 2 anterolateral teeth convex; well defined posterolateral tooth behind branchial notch.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E1CF661C061A2E56FF18FA05FCAF222C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501118" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6501118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501118/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="349" startId="48.[151,250,1834,1858]" targetBox="[151,1435,904,1811]" targetPageId="48">
<paragraph id="B50F3694061A2E56FF18FA05FCAF222C" blockId="48.[151,1437,1834,1895]" pageId="48" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061A2E56FF18FA05FEF12208" bold="true" box="[151,283,1834,1858]" pageId="48" pageNumber="349">FIGURE 32</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061A2E56FEA6FA05FD692209" authority="(Gray 1831)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[297,643,1834,1859]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Stimdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061A2E56FEA6FA05FE102208" box="[297,506,1834,1858]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="349">Stimdromia lateralis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65061A2E56FD86FA04FD912209" author="Gray, J. E." box="[521,635,1835,1859]" pageId="48" pageNumber="349" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref25930" refString="Gray, J. E. (1831) Description of a new genus, and some undescribed species of Crustacea. Zoological Miscellany, 1, 39 - 40." type="journal article" year="1831">Gray 1831</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, male, 17.0 × 15.0 mm (WAM 65-83): A, dorsal view; B, ventral view (with sponge cap); C, frontal view; D, ventral view oral and sternal areas.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B50F3694061A2E57FF48FABAFC8F25B3" blockId="48.[151,1436,1941,2039]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1437,150,609]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="350" pageId="48" pageNumber="349">Chelipeds well developed, tubercular, inner surface of carpus and propodus densely setose, dorsal surface tends to be flattened with poorly defined ridge running along inner border; fingers white and gaping. Outer face of cheliped propodus sometimes with fine tubercles tending to be arranged in longitudinal rows. P2 and P3 also with strong distal tubercles on dorsal margins. P4 and P 5 smaller, dactyli opposed by single propodal spine with another similar spine on outer propodal margin. Posterior margin of telson broadly rounded, subtruncate. Female thoracic sternal grooves ending well apart on small tubercles between P2 coxae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAA651F061B2E57FF48FC2CFBAC249B" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B50F3694061B2E57FF48FC2CFB06240B" blockId="49.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FF48FC2CFEDE2457" bold="true" box="[199,308,259,285]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Remarks</emphasis>
. The true identity of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061B2E57FDA9FC2CFCC32457" box="[550,809,259,285]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FDA9FC2CFCC32457" box="[550,809,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Cryptodromia lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was uncertain until 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65061B2E57FB9FFC2CFB2D2457" author="Stimpson, W." box="[1040,1223,259,285]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" pagination="1 - 240" refId="ref30116" refString="Stimpson, W. (1907) Report on the Crustacea (Brachyura and Anomura) collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, 1853 - 1856. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 49 (1717), 1 - 240. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 51448" type="journal article" year="1907">Stimpson (1907</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 20 fig. 3) published a figure of this species, based on material collected from Port Jackson, i.e., Sydney Harbour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B50F3694061B2E57FF48FC64FBAC249B" blockId="49.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">
The differences between 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061B2E57FE6FFC64FDB2242F" box="[480,600,331,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FE6FFC64FDB2242F" box="[480,600,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">S. lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061B2E57FD01FC64FCFE242F" baseAuthorityName="Ortmann" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[654,788,331,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Stimdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FD01FC64FCFE242F" box="[654,788,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">S. lamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include: carapace tomentose and smooth (versus bare and granular in 
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FE99FC40FE4924C3" box="[278,419,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061B2E57FE99FC40FE7124C3" baseAuthorityName="Ortmann" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[278,411,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Stimdromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellata">S. lamellata</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
; rostral teeth unequal (versus teeth approximately same size); anterolateral carapace margin armed with two teeth (versus three irregular teeth); cheliped and P1 and P2 tubercular on distal ends of carpi and propodi (versus crest-like). Brood young are carried by female (
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65061B2E57FCEDFC98FBD3249B" author="Montgomery, S. K." box="[866,1081,439,465]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" pagination="193 - 196" refId="ref28677" refString="Montgomery, S. K. (1922) Direct development of a dromiid crab. Proceedings of the Zoological Society London, 13, 193 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1922. tb 03305. x" type="journal article" year="1922">Montgomery 1922</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAA651F061B2E57FF48FCF5FD96272B" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B50F3694061B2E57FF48FCF5FD96272B" blockId="49.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FF48FCF5FE8B24BE" bold="true" box="[199,353,474,500]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604061B2E57FE61FCF4FDB224BF" box="[494,600,475,501]" name="Australia" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Australia</collectingCountry>
, found around most of the coastline. Old records of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604061B2E57FAE8FCF4FF1B2753" name="New Zealand" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
refer to 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061B2E57FEDCFCD0FCAC2753" authority="(Fulton &amp; Grant, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="Fulton &amp; Grant" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[339,838,511,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Metadromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilsoni">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FEDCFCD0FDDF2753" box="[339,565,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Metadromia wilsoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65061B2E57FDCBFCD0FCD42753" author="Fulton S. W. &amp; Grant, F. E." box="[580,830,511,537]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" pagination="59 - 68" refId="ref25718" refString="Fulton S. W. &amp; Grant, F. E. (1902) Some little known Victorian decapod Crustacea with description of new species, no. 2. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 15, 59 - 68." type="journal article" year="1902">Fulton &amp; Grant, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Miers’ (1884) records of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D17061B2E57FBE2FCD0FB0D2753" box="[1133,1255,511,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FBE2FCD0FB0D2753" box="[1133,1255,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">S. lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="7774F876061B2E57FE93FF0CFE892777" box="[284,355,547,573]" country="Philippines" name="Bohol" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Bohol</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604061B2E57FEFEFF0CFE052777" box="[369,495,547,573]" name="Philippines" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and Madjicasima, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA77604061B2E57FD43FF0CFCE52777" box="[716,783,547,573]" name="Japan" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Japan</collectingCountry>
, (HMS 
<emphasis id="87C4EA86061B2E57FCE3FF0CFC352777" box="[876,991,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="350">Samarang</emphasis>
) in the NHM need verification. Depth range: 
<quantity id="72489B71061B2E57FF6BFF68FEAD272B" box="[228,327,583,609]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.105" metricValueMax="2.21" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" unit="m" value="110.5" valueMax="221.0" valueMin="0.0">0–221 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B65061B2E57FEDAFF68FD9A272B" author="Farrelly, C. A. &amp; Ahyong, S. T." box="[341,624,583,609]" pageId="49" pageNumber="350" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref25650" refString="Farrelly, C. A. &amp; Ahyong, S. T. (2019) Deepwater decapod, stomatopod and lophogastrid Crustacea from Eastern Australia and the Great Australian Bight collected in 2015 - 2017: preliminary identifications of 191 species. Museum Victoria Science Reports, 21, 1 - 97. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mvsr. 2019.21" type="journal article" year="2019">Farrelly &amp; Ahyong 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
